<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 22 at 2:41PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Fergus
County through 315 PM MDT...
At 240 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles east of Roy, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central Fergus
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
